  "text": "DRG2 antibodies (antiserum no. 55) were generated by immunizing rabbits with a His-tagged fusion protein containing the N-terminal 202 residues of pea DRG2 [CITATION_1] ). The entire 369-residue coding region of AtDRG1 was cloned into pQE30 (Qiagen) in order to generate a fusion protein containing a His-tag at its N-terminus. Forward and reverse PCR primers corresponding to the AtDRG1 cDNA were used to amplify the entire coding region (AGAGGATCC-ATGTCGACTATTATGCAGAAG and CATGGTACCTCATAT-CTTTTTAACGATCTGAACAAC, respectively). A cDNA clone was used as a template (clone M70O01 in pBlueScript SK À from ABRC). Rabbits were immunized by injecting antigen into surgically implanted ball chambers [CITATION_2] . DRG1 antibodies (antiserum no. 29) were affinity purified using an AffiGel-10 column (BioRad) to which DRG1-His had been covalently bound.",
